{
  "texts": [
    "This selection is performed using the lensfit contamination_radius parameter, contamination_radius > 4.",
    "25 pix, (33) and removes sources that are contaminated by extracted neighbours.",
    "This selection removed 26.3% of the MASK ≤ 1 sample; however, most of these sources are already removed by previous selections (particularly the 'unmeasured' selection).",
    "As such, this blending selection only removes a further 6.99% of the available sample.As described in Sect. 7.1, the lensfit code provides a range of flags related to the quality of the fitted model, called fitclass.",
    "fitclass selection is particularly useful for the rejection of point-like sources from the sample, which might otherwise contaminate our lensing measurements."
  ]
}